SIMPLE: double_standard
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: double standard
<hw>dou"ble stan"dard</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a standard
or set of principles governing conduct, which is applied more
stringently or differently to one group of people than to another; --
used especially of standards of sexual behavior that condemn behavior on
the part of women that is condoned or not condemned when exhibited by
men.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Double-surfaced</ent>⟦br⟧
